Key Match Events: Antonín Barák’s early sending off made life too hard for the Czech Republic to get the win they needed, as Turkey booked their place in the last 16
Arda Güler missed a gilt-edged chance to settle things midway through the second half
Tomáš Souček equalised for the battling ten men
Cenk Tosun sealed it at the death
Post-Match Reflections: Turkey were the more creative side, and deserved their victory overall
Turkey will play Austria in Leipzig next Tuesday; one of Turkey, Austria, Romania and the Netherlands will make it to the semis
The ten men gave it a brave go, but they’ll be heading home
